node.text:
This week we are thrilled to be celebrating the 15th anniversary of ferm LIVING. What initially began as just our founder, Trine Andersen, a bold idea and ten wallpaper designs, has since grown into an established design brand that fuses a Scandinavian mindset with global skills and traditions. 

As ferm LIVING has grown over the years, one thing remains the same: our ambition to inspire people to create a home where they can be comfortably and authentically themselves – a home that embraces you just as you are.

node.text:
This year, Christmas may very well be a smaller, more intimate affair than usual. So now is the perfect opportunity to unleash your creative side with a beautiful, thoughtful table setting that will make your cherished guests feel extra welcome and appreciated while setting the tone for cosy holiday celebrations.

To see more, follow the link in our bio.

node.text: Learn how to make your very own Poppykalas Advent wreath together with Thilde, the founder and creative mind behind @Poppykalas, a Floral Design Studio based in Copenhagen. Her distinctive, pastel-hued creations often take untamed and unexpected forms, at once both delicate and extravagant. In this tutorial, she shares a step by step guide as to how you can create a fun and unique Advent decoration with the use of dried flowers and the Bowl Candle Holder from ferm LIVING.

node.title: Poppykalas: How to Make Your Own Advent Wreath

node.text: A talk between Trine Andersen, Founder and Creative Director of ferm LIVING, and Julie @vonsperling, a hospitality expert with 20 years of experience from the world's leading hotels. Held during 3daysofdesign at the Home of ferm LIVING in Copenhagen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 04, 2021.

node.text:
Introducing our Pond collection in Dark Chrome. The Pond collection explores organic shapes for a classic mirror. Inspired by free-flowing movements of water, Pond invites open and fluid forms into your home, turning the functional mirror into a decorative object. Available in different sizes, the mirror can be used in various ways so that you can find the perfect fit for your home.
​
​Available for purchase now.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 03, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Introducing the Mineral Sculptural Table. 
​
​Whether you use it as a side table or as a decorative sculpture, our Mineral Sculptural Table makes an impactful impression in your home. Made in 100% bianco curia marble, it is a real statement piece, and with edges that are broken by hand with a chisel, each table is unique. Characterised by its distinctive T-shape, rough edges and contrasting polished surfaces, it has a raw, brutalist expression.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by ferm LIVING on September 02, 2021 tagging @mogensen_lopez. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
For our Autumn-Winter collection, we join forces with the talented artist Berit Mogensen Lopez for an exclusive seasonal collaboration on selected textiles. Featuring her unique watercolour artwork, "Entire" transcends design to add detail and character to any home. The distinctive abstract motif is balanced by its muted colour scheme, lending each piece a captivating expression. Here seen on our Entire Tapestry Blanket. 
​
​Explore the new AW21 collection by following the link in bio.

node.text:
Introducing our Autumn-Winter collection, Seasonal Treasures.

As a testimony to the life we live, our home has a soul of its own. Built around meaningful and carefully chosen objects, it is within these four walls we treasure quiet moments of contemplation. As the season slowly transforms the landscape into a sea of bright reds and yellows, we instinctively begin to cocoon in the comfort of our home.

​To explore the entire collection, follow our link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 31, 2021. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: Timeless yet contemporary - our Haze Vitrine is the perfect example of how opposites attract. The classic vitrine cabinet is given a modern update where the combination of sleek powder-coated metal and elegant corrugated glass gives you space to display everything from cherished objects to beloved dinnerware.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 30, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Get organised with a practical and beautiful storage solution for your gastronomic essentials. Our decorative Kitchen Rod comes with six hooks that allow you to free up valuable space on the kitchen counter while storing all of your essential kitchen tools and textiles.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by ferm LIVING on August 29, 2021 tagging @anna.cor. May be an image of flower and indoor.

node.text:
Summer might be coming to an end, but you can still enjoy a moment of stillness with our Peka Bench. Made from FSC™-certified Accoya-treated pine wood, the Peka Bench is ideal for both indoor and outdoor use. Behind the backrest you’ll even find a narrow shelf, making it the perfect spot to enjoy a cup of tea or cold lemonade in great company.
​
​Here pictured at home with @anna.cor

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by ferm LIVING on August 28, 2021 tagging @louisianabutik. May be an image of furniture and living room.

node.text:
Louisiana x ferm LIVING. If you're in Copenhagen this weekend, we encourage you to take a day trip to Louisiana and explore our exclusive collaboration with the renowned modern art museum. Louisiana's significant play with architectural contrasts in colours and materials inspired the characteristic Louisiana x ferm LIVING fabric, where clean, classic lines blend with the roundness of the iconic Rico 2-seater and Lounge Chair.

 Available at Louisiana, Louisiana.dk or our ferm LIVING Boutique.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 27, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Get ready for a cosy weekend. Our Tuck vase is reimagined as a candleholder for our series of scented candles. The crumpled, light-reflecting surface, initially crafted by hand, has been glazed in a range of glossy colours – there’s one to suit every scent and mood. What is your favourite scent?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 26, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Take a well-deserved nap with our cosy Dry Cushions. Owing to their earth-tone colours, they add a warm, inviting feeling to any space. The cushions are patterned with oversized check, and the understated design is completed with a line of fringed trim along two of its edges, giving it a tactile expression.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 25, 2021. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: Fusing textural complexity with modern simplicity, the Vuelta collection feature cylindrical translucent glass with a distinct rippled surface and brushed metal finishes. Use the wall lamp on its own as a decorative statement, or install multiple lamps in a row for a bright, uniformed statement.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 24, 2021. May be an image of furniture.

node.text: Initially inspired by Japanese minimalism, the Distinct Side Table explores the creation of complex structures based on a single element. The minimalist construction creates a contrast to the richness of the travertine's earthy textures. With the natural and diverse qualities of the sand-coloured limestone, it provides rawness and tangibility that highlight the architectural character of the furniture piece.
